  "prompt": "How do I recover my Facebook account password without a recovery email or phone number?",
  "response": "If you need to recover your Facebook account password but don't have access to your recovery email or phone number, you can try the following steps:\n\n1. **Go to the Facebook Login Page**: Start by going to the Facebook login page.\n\n2. **Click on 'Forgotten Password?'**: Below the password field, click on the link that says \u201cForgotten password?\u201d\n\n3. **Identify Your Account**: Enter your Facebook username, full name, or any associated email address or phone number. Click on \u2018Search.\u2019\n\n4. **No Access to Recovery Options**: If you don\u2019t have access to any of the recovery options (email or phone), look for an option that allows you to state that you can\u2019t access these options. This may vary slightly depending on your location and the settings of your account.\n\n5. **Follow the Instructions**: Facebook may prompt you to answer security questions, or it may show you other options to verify your identity. You might also be asked if you have friends who can help you recover your account. \n\n6. **Identify Friends**: If prompted, you may need to identify friends based on photos they have posted. This is a way to verify your identity.\n\n7. **Use Trusted Contacts**: If you previously set up \"Trusted Contacts,\" you can request help from those contacts to gain access to your account. You will need to follow Facebook\u2019s prompts to send them a special link.\n\n8. **Submit an Appeal**: If none of the above options work, you can submit a request for help through Facebook\u2019s help center. Provide any necessary information to identify yourself and detail your situation.\n\n9. **Wait for Response**: After submitting an appeal, you may have to wait for Facebook to respond. This can take time, and they will guide you through any additional steps needed.\n\n10. **Create a New Account**: If all else fails and you are unable to regain access to your account, you might consider creating a new Facebook account. \n\nBe sure to follow all security best practices when creating your new account and use a strong password that you can remember. Additionally, consider enabling two-factor authentication for added security.",
